body:
When automatically generating specs from source, special chars are stripped from the beginning of lines. Is this intended? I was trying to use Markdown to document the API metadata, as the Swagger UI is able to render markdown.

So, my code looks like that:

``` go
// #video-transcoding-api
//
// HTTP API for transcoding media files into different formats using pluggable
// providers.
//
// ##Currently supported providers
//
// * [Amazon Elastic Transcoder](https://aws.amazon.com/elastictranscoder/)
// * [Elemental Conductor](https://www.elementaltechnologies.com/products/elemental-conductor)
// * [Encoding.com](http://api.encoding.com)
//
// [...]
//
// swagger:meta
package main
```

And the result is the following:

``` json
{
  [...]
  "info": {
    "description": "HTTP API for transcoding media files into different formats using pluggable\nproviders.\n\nCurrently supported providers\n\nAmazon Elastic Transcoder](https://aws.amazon.com/elastictranscoder/)\nElemental Conductor](https://www.elementaltechnologies.com/products/elemental-conductor)\nEncoding.com](http://api.encoding.com)",
    [...]
  }
}
```

And here is how it's displayed on Swagger UI:

<img width="971" alt="swagger-ui-markdown" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/108725/13016371/7d20eb40-d1a5-11e5-9968-4ac5c8a11b29.png">

I can work on a pull request if this is not intended behavior.
